text: Shemshak darbandsar () is a city in Rudbar-e Qasran District, Shemiranat County, Tehran Province, Iran. At the 2006 census, its population was 2,383, in 702 families. The city of Shemshak darbandsar was formed from the former villages of Shemshak-e Bala, Shemshak-e Pain, Darband Sar, Sefidestan, Darrud, and Jirud. ==References== Category:Populated places in Shemiranat County Category:Cities in Tehran Province
